# ── .dockerignore ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Whitelist-style: exclude everything, then allow only paths needed by Dockerfiles.
# Applies when build context is the repo root (services use context: ../.. ).
#
# worldview-web also builds from repo root (context: ../..); its files are
# whitelisted below. intelligence-migrations uses its own build context.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Exclude everything by default
*

# ── Shared libraries (pyproject.toml + src only) ──────────────────────────────
!libs/common/pyproject.toml
!libs/common/src/
!libs/contracts/pyproject.toml
!libs/contracts/src/
!libs/messaging/pyproject.toml
!libs/messaging/src/
!libs/observability/pyproject.toml
!libs/observability/src/
!libs/storage/pyproject.toml
!libs/storage/src/
!libs/ml-clients/pyproject.toml
!libs/ml-clients/src/
!libs/prompts/pyproject.toml
!libs/prompts/src/
!libs/tools/pyproject.toml
!libs/tools/src/

# ── Service source + build metadata ──────────────────────────────────────────
!services/*/pyproject.toml
!services/*/src/
!services/*/alembic/
!services/*/alembic.ini
!services/*/Dockerfile
# F-502 (QA iter-5): ship operator one-shots (backfills, repairs) into the
# image so SREs can run them via `docker compose exec` rather than `docker cp`.
# Whitelisted at the service level — any service that has a scripts/ directory
# gets it baked into its image automatically.
!services/*/scripts/

# ── Kafka Avro schemas (needed by consumers at runtime) ──────────────────────
!infra/kafka/schemas/

# ── Frontend (worldview-web Dockerfile also uses repo root context) ──────────
!package.json
!pnpm-workspace.yaml
!pnpm-lock.yaml
!apps/worldview-web/
# Re-exclude local build artifacts that the whitelist above would otherwise pull
# in: apps/worldview-web/.next is ~1.7 GB of local dev-build output. Shipping it
# bloated the context ~40x AND let the Docker build reuse STALE compiled chunks
# (a fresh source edit didn't appear in the image). The Dockerfile runs its own
# pnpm install + next build, so neither is needed from the context.
apps/worldview-web/.next/
apps/worldview-web/.next
apps/worldview-web/node_modules/
apps/worldview-web/node_modules

# ── Re-exclude dev artifacts that snuck through the above globs ──────────────
**/.mypy_cache
**/.pytest_cache
**/.venv
**/__pycache__
**/*.pyc
**/*.pyo
